data.title: Humphrey Bogart
data.meta_description: The Official Website of the Humphrey Bogart Estate
data.text: From the 1920s until the 1950s, Humphrey Bogart’s film career covered virtually every genre from crime dramas to musicals. His various roles have given the world some of the most memorable characters, including Sam Spade, Duke Mantee, Charlie Allnut, Rick Blaine. Philip Marlowe, and Fred C. Dobbs, among countless others. Bogie’s filmography is not only a testament to his ability as an actor, but a timeline illustrating his humble beginnings and eventual rise to superstardom.
